n)` section below. The same-day A13 detail is retained inline next.) ⟢ (A13 run — Lens A Hub security & auth; **GREEN held, and the formal A-pass F11 asked for is now done** — the `⚠ pre-HubV3` flag on A is **cleared**. F11 downgraded F to YELLOW because the +71-commit HubV3 surface had had no A/B pass; A13 gives it the A pass on deploy-truth bytes (`origin/main@926dda41`, +76 since A12). **i3x external Bearer-key API (12 read routes) — SOLID:** `resolveI3xTenant` (`lib/i3x/auth.ts`) stores **only** `sha256(key)` (mig 054 `key_hash UNIQUE`), looks it up **parameterized** under the owner pool, returns null→**401**, **never logs plaintext**, then every data read runs under **`withTenantContext` RLS** and exposes **only `approval_state='verified'`** kg_entities (`i3x/v1/objects` confirmed); revocation works via `enabled=false` (checked in both the SQL and `resolveTenantFromKeyRow`). Key **issuance is out-of-band** — there is **no self-serve key endpoint** in `api/i3x` (all 12 routes are READ), which is *good* (no abusable mint path) but means key **entropy is unverifiable** in-repo. **Two i3x defense-in-depth gaps (non-blocking):** the `i3x_api_keys` table has **no `expires_at`** (keys are non-expiring; revocation is the only kill-switch) and there is **no app-level rate-limit** on the Bearer routes (mitigated *iff* keys are high-entropy — recommend an `openssl rand -hex 32` issuance standard + an `expires_at` column). **Contextualization (10 routes) — SOLID:** `/import` (JSON intake-contract **or** multipart `.zip`) is **`sessionOr401`-gated**, runs under `withTenantContext`, and **explicitly stays OFF `knowledge_entries`** (code comment cites the tenant-scoping rule → the `is_private` hybrid-corpus footgun is avoided by construction); the `.zip` is parsed **in memory** to a `Record<name,Buffer>` (`unzip.ts` — never writes to the filesystem → **no zip-slip**); `/[id]/promote` validates the id against a **UUID regex**, is **double tenant-scoped**, and **STAGES** into `kg_entities@proposed` + `ai_suggestions@pending` — it **never auto-verifies** and **refuses to overwrite** `verified/deprecated` rows; the publish gate `/batches/[batchId]/review` routes `proposed→verified` through the **ADR-0017 helper `applyHubProposalTransition`** (not a raw `UPDATE`), only inside the human `decision==='approve'` branch, with a no-overwrite guard. **Migrations:** **054** intentionally has **no RLS** (key table resolved *before* a tenant context exists — documented, correct); **055 + 056** are textbook per `mira-hub-migrations.md` — `ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY` + `CREATE POLICY tenant_isolation_*` with **in-type `::UUID`** comparison + `GRANT … TO factorylm_app` + `IF NOT EXISTS`/`DROP POLICY IF EXISTS` idempotent + single `BEGIN/COMMIT` txn + sha256 dedup unique indexes. **ONE actionable finding (A13-1, availability hardening — NOT a leak):** the `/import` **`.zip` bundle path inflates entries via `inflateRawSync(data)` with no `maxOutputLength` cap and no `file.size` pre-check**, while the sibling single-file `/[id]/sources` route **does** cap (413 over `MAX_UPLOAD_BYTES`). An **authenticated** tenant can upload a small decompression-bomb `.zip` that inflates to GBs and **OOM the shared hub** (DoS for all tenants on the box). It is `sessionOr401`-gated (not anonymous) and writes only tenant-scoped `ctx_*` rows → it **"breaks," it does not "leak"** ⇒ **YELLOW-grade**, not RED. **Patch staged:** `patches/2026-06-21-A13-contextualization-zipbomb-cap.patch` (adds per-entry `maxOutputLength` + total-inflated + entry-count caps to `unzip.ts`; follow-up note to mirror the 413 size-check into `importFromBundle`). **Verdict: A stays GREEN** (confidentiality + integrity intact: no cross-tenant read, no IDOR, no auto-verify, RLS+GRANT correct), the `⚠ pre-HubV3` asterisk is **removed**, and the **security half** of F's coverage gap is **closed** — F can recover to GREEN once **B** audits the contextualization *functional* half and the orientation docs are refreshed. Scorecard holds **4G/2Y/0R** (D + F the YELLOWs). **KG insight:** the nightly graph (4,157n/77,335e, kg_query, built from the 79-behind tree) splits the two HubV3 surfaces **exactly along the audit's risk line** — `resolveI3xTenant` + `applyHubProposalTransition` + `withTenantContext` + `sessionOr401` each **resolve (1 hit)**, so i3x's auth + the contextualization *publish* spine are **graph-visible**, but the contextualization **intake** half (`importFromBundle`, `readZipEntries`) returns **0 hits** — and the **single A13 finding lives precisely in that un-graphed intake half**, while the publish path A12 already proved sound is the graph-present half. Code-nav could "see" the part that was already safe and was blind to the part that carried the defect. i3x is also the **only** new surface that stands up a genuinely **new auth primitive** (the Bearer key) — so that bespoke-auth island is where residual i3x risk (no expiry/no rate-limit) concentrates; contextualization adds **no** new auth primitive, so its only residual risk is **availability** (the zip-bomb), not confidentiality. Rotation **Round 13 → B next** [audit the 10 contextualization routes' functional/data-shape correctness — the half F11 deferred to "then B"].) · deploy truth `origin/main@926dda41`

