**Overall (Round 13 · E12):** **4 GREEN (A, B, C, E) · 2 YELLOW (D, F) · 0 RED — held.** E12 re-audits the promotion pipeline on deploy truth and **holds Lens E GREEN**, and the run's headline is a real pipeline improvement: of the **103** commits since E11 (`529d62e2`), only **2** touch E-scope (`.github/workflows/`+compose), and the first — `ffcc8636` "pin prod VPS to release tag, not main HEAD" — **closes the standing F11 ledger item #7 (#736)**. `deploy-vps.yml`'s deploy step now resolves the `vX.Y.Z` tag that `version-tag.yml` lays on each merge commit (`git tag --points-at origin/main 'v[0-9]*' | sort -V | tail -1`) and `checkout --force`s it, with a graceful fallback to `git reset --hard origin/main` if the tag is lagging — so production references a **real, immutable rollback anchor** (the gap `docs/versioning.md` flagged and `docs/runbooks/hubv3-rollback.md` ROLLBACK-A depends on) instead of a moving `main` HEAD. The second E-scope commit (`faba7d1b`) only inlines a dead mira-ingest HTTP worker in `docker-compose.saas.yml`/`mira-core` compose — not a gate change. **The two-gate deploy is intact and, if anything, stronger on deploy-truth bytes:** `deploy-vps.yml` ships only when the `Smoke Test` `workflow_run` reports `conclusion=='success'` **and** a "Verify Staging Gate passed" step maps the deploy SHA back to its source PR and confirms the Staging Gate ran green on that PR head — a commit with **no associated PR (a direct push to main) is refused**, and the only bypass (`skip_staging_gate`) requires a written reason that auto-files an audit issue. `smoke-test.yml` exercises both `factorylm.com` and `app.factorylm.com` plus the full signup money-path (`playwright.signup.config.ts`) and the `/quickstart` P1-1 public grounded-chat answer, so a beta tester's exact path is gated end-to-end before any deploy. The hub migration head has advanced **055→056** (`056_contextualization_intake`); the **double-055 prefix** is the expected **cosmetic** artifact of two parallel branches landing — `apply-migrations.yml` keys the ledger on the full basename, so per `mira-hub-migrations.md` it must **not** be renumbered. **What keeps the lens from being "nothing to report" is persistent doc-hygiene drift, all non-blocking:** `CLAUDE.md` L45/L47 still tag `docker-compose.staging.yml` and `@MiraStagingBot` `*(TODO)*` even though both exist (the staged `2026-06-19-E10-…staging-todo-stale.patch` is re-verified `git apply --check` CLEAN against origin/main this run and just needs a founder merge), `hot.md`'s top is an epoch stale (06-12), and the Gap-5 staging-HTTPS cutover is a one-shot founder task that is **staging-QA convenience, not stranger-facing** (beta testers sign up on prod, which smoke covers). **KG insight:** the recurring **present-target / missing-gate-edge** fingerprint holds — `kg_query.py` on the 4,475-node graph returns **0 hits** for all five promotion-gate workflows (`deploy-vps`/`smoke-test`/`staging-gate`/`migration-verify`/`beta-gate`) while the deploy *targets* `sessionOr401`/`withTenantContext` each resolve, so the entire pin-to-tag gate change is **invisible to code navigation and provable only by reading `deploy-vps.yml` bytes** (graphify remains UNINSTALLABLE here — no module/CLI, all five LLM keys unset — so the +13/+6 E-scope nodes/edges are hand-extracted into `kg/e12-findings.jsonl`). **Scorecard holds 4 GREEN (A,B,C,E) / 2 YELLOW (D,F) / 0 RED.** **Rotation Round 13 → F next** (F11 06-20 now oldest; F re-ranks the beta-blocker ledger now that #736 is off it, and should refresh the epoch-stale orientation docs).

