n approval), not stranger-facing, so it doesn't move the beta gate — hence **B stays GREEN with a logged coverage watch-item**, and the `⚠ pre-HubV3` flag is cleared. Staged fix: `patches/2026-06-21-B12-review-publish-gate-integration-test.patch` (a real route-handler integration test for the publish gate, modeled byte-for-byte on the one good harness, integration-lane so it doesn't touch the offline scorecard count). **KG insight:** the publish gate's own dependency graph splits **exactly along the test-coverage line** — the nightly graphify build resolves `applyHubProposalTransition` (the shared ADR-0017 spine, the half A12/A13 already proved sound) but returns **0 node hits** for the ctx-local decision functions it calls (`decideBatchReview`/`decidePublish`/`buildEntityInsert`/`buildPublishEntityUpdate`) — the same present-target/missing-newest fingerprint A10/B11/E10/F11/A13 keep surfacing, now localized to the publish gate's route handler (hand-extracted into `kg/lens-b-contextualization-supplement.json`). **F can recover to GREEN** once the orientation docs (`known-issues.md`, `hot.md`) are refreshed past the HubV3 epoch (mig head still implies ~037 vs the real 056) — both A's security half and B's functional half of its coverage gap are now closed. D stays YELLOW (eval noise, founder-keyed). **Rotation Round 13 → C next** (engine integrity re-verify).

