## Lens B — Hub functional readiness (B12, this run): GREEN held (⚠ pre-HubV3 cleared)

**Audited `origin/main@f6a9bec2` (working tree 80 behind — STALE; all reads via `git show origin/main:`).** Scope: the HubV3 **contextualization functional half** F11 deferred and A13 (security half) handed off — 10 `/api/contextualization/*` routes, `/api/assets/[id]/context`, `lib/contextualization/*`.

### Functional verdict — CORRECT on deploy truth (no defect)

- **Every route is access-gated + tenant-scoped.** All 10 ctx routes use `sessionOr401` + `withTenantContext`; `assets/[id]/context` uses `sessionOrDemo` + `withTenantContext`. Methods: 1 WRITE (`batches/[batchId]/review` POST), the rest GET.
- **The ADR-0017 publish gate is exemplary.** `batches/[batchId]/review` (POST) validates `batchId` against a UUID regex (400), parses+validates `decision` (400), 503-guards on missing DB, 404s a missing/foreign-tenant batch. On `approve` **only**, it publishes accepted extractions (`status='accepted' AND uns_path_proposed IS NOT NULL`, joined via `ctx_sources.import_batch_id`, tenant-scoped) into `kg_entities`: `decidePublish` chooses insert-as-`verified` / guarded-update / **skip**, and `verified`/`deprecated` rows are **never overwritten** (skip → `reason:"protected — not overwritten"`). It then moves the paired `ai_suggestions` row pending→accepted **through `applyHubProposalTransition`** (the ADR-0017 helper, **not** a raw `UPDATE`) so the `/proposals` queue and the live model stay in lockstep. No path auto-verifies; human approve *is* the verification.
- **Stays off the hybrid corpus.** `/import` is tenant-scoped and **explicitly does not touch `knowledge_entries`** (code comment cites the tenant-scoping rule) — the #1833/#1761 footgun is avoided by construction.

### Finding B12-1 (test-integrity, non-blocking) — the publish gate has no route-level test

The single most consequential **write** in the contextualization surface — the `proposed→verified` publish + `ai_suggestions` lockstep — has **zero route-handler test**. And the surrounding "coverage" is thinner than the filenames imply:

| Route (method) | Test file | What it actually exercises |
|---|---|---|
| `contextualization/route` (POST/GET) | `route.test.ts` | imports `parseCreateBody` — **one real exported helper** (not the handler) |
| `[id]/sources` (GET) | `route.test.ts` | imports `sourceTypeFor` — **one real exported helper** |
| `import` (POST) | `import.integration.test.ts` | **imports `POST` — the ONE genuine route-handler test** |
| `[id]/export` (GET) | `route.test.ts` | **shadow** — re-declares 4 helpers locally, asserts on the copy |
| `[id]/extractions/[eid]` (GET) | `route.test.ts` | **shadow** — re-declares 1 helper locally |
| `[id]/promote` (POST) | `route.test.ts` | **shadow** — re-declares `unsPathToLtree`/`clampConfidence` locally |
| **`batches/[batchId]/review` (POST)** | **— none —** | **publish gate: 0 route + 0 shadow** |
| `batches/[batchId]` (GET) | — none — | RLS read, untested |
| `batches` (GET) | — none — | RLS read, untested |
| `[id]/extractions` (GET) | — none — | RLS read, untested |
| `assets/[id]/context` (GET) | — none — | RLS read, `sessionOrDemo` — verify demo can't cross tenants |

The publish gate's *decision logic* IS genuinely covered — `approval.test.ts` (15) + `acceptance-matrix.test.ts` (13) test the real `approval.ts` (`decideBatchReview`/`decidePublish`/`buildEntityInsert`/`buildPublishEntityUpdate`). The gap is purely the **route wiring**: tenant-scoped SQL, the `applyHubProposalTransition` lockstep, the insert/update/skip no-overwrite branches, and the 400/404/503/500 envelope are unexercised. Because it's operator-facing (admin approval), not stranger-facing, it does **not** move the beta gate — hence **YELLOW-grade watch-item, not a downgrade**. **Staged fix:** `patches/2026-06-21-B12-review-publish-gate-integration-test.patch` — a real route-handler integration test (`import { POST }`, mocked session, Postgres test DB) modeled byte-for-byte on `import.integration.test.ts`, covering approve-publishes-verified, no-overwrite-protects, reject/needs_review-no-publish, cross-tenant-404, bad-decision/id-400. It is `*.integration.test.ts` (integration lane) so it **does not change the offline scorecard count**.

### tsc

`mira-hub/node_modules/.bin/tsc` is present, **but only on the 80-behind working tree** — a `tsc --noEmit` there would typecheck stale bytes, not deploy truth, so it's not run this round (a deploy-truth typecheck needs a detached `origin/main` worktree; out of this run's time budget). B11 already verified tsc-clean and #2127 removed the 2 stale `@ts-expect-error`.

### KG insight

The publish gate's dependency graph splits **exactly along the test-coverage line**: the nightly graphify build (`kg/graph.json`, 4,168 nodes, 06-20) resolves `applyHubProposalTransition` (1 hit — the shared ADR-0017 spine A12/A13 already proved sound) but returns **0 node hits** for the four ctx-local decision functions the route calls (`decideBatchReview`/`decidePublish`/`buildEntityInsert`/`buildPublishEntityUpdate`) and **0** for `ctx_import_batches`. Code-nav can see the publish gate's shared spine and is blind to its local decision layer — the same half that's test-orphaned. Hand-extracted into `kg/lens-b-contextualization-supplement.json` (15 nodes / 10 edges, deploy truth).

### Carried from B11

`WhyMiraThinksThis` decision-trace panel still has 0 e2e refs (API unit tests only) — add a Playwright render proof.

