## Lens F — Beta-blocker ledger (F10, this run): GREEN → YELLOW (A10 leak ranked #1; closes Round 10)

Re-synthesized on deploy truth (`origin/main@944ef64d`; freshness-guard exit 3 STALE, but every
F-scope doc matches origin/main byte-for-byte). Baseline F9@`11348efc` (2026-06-17). F's job is the
**ranked ledger + the North-Star verdict** ("a stranger can sign up, use grounded chat, and nothing
breaks, leaks, or lies"). The material change since F9: **A10 (#2044) was discovered 06-18, one day
after F9 ran** — so this is the first F-pass that must carry it, and it is a real, stranger-reachable
confidentiality **leak**, which downgrades F to YELLOW.

### North-Star verdict on deploy truth: breaks NO · lies NO · **leaks YES (A10, patch staged)**

- **Breaks?** No. The stranger upload→retrieval→citation flow is structurally protected and
  CI-guarded: `tests/beta/beta_ready_upload_retrieval_citation.py` (xfail removed #2077) runs in
  `beta-gate.yml` weekly + on gate-path PRs; #2099 embed-on-write makes the stranger's own upload
  retrievable on write (closes the dark-chunk failure for the beta path).
- **Lies?** No. Citation enforcement is default-on (C10 re-verified), groundedness scoring intact,
  cross-vendor citation canonicalization (#2083) strengthens grounding.
- **Leaks?** **Yes — A10.** `git show origin/main:mira-hub/src/app/api/knowledge/search/route.ts`:
  docstring L10 literally "no tenant filter"; `pool.query` (owner pool, BYPASSRLS) runs a
  `content_tsv @@ plainto_tsquery` search **and** an ILIKE fallback over `knowledge_entries` with
  **no `is_private` and no tenant predicate**. Migration 052 (`privatize-node-attachment-chunks`)
  proves `is_private=true` per-tenant uploads live in that same table. ⇒ any authed beta tenant's
  knowledge-library search returns other tenants' **private manual snippets**. Fix written +
  apply-check CLEAN: `patches/2026-06-18-A10-knowledge-search-is-private-leak.patch`.

### Ranked beta-blocker ledger (top-8, deploy truth `origin/main@944ef64d`)

| # | Blocker | Class | Status | Exact next action |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| **1** | **A10 / #2044 — `/api/knowledge/search` cross-tenant content leak** | 🔴 confidentiality (stranger-reachable) | OPEN; patch staged, apply-check CLEAN | **Merge** `patches/2026-06-18-A10-knowledge-search-is-private-leak.patch` (adds `AND is_private = false` to both the tsquery + ILIKE branches). Flips A **and** F to GREEN. |
| **2** | **#2093 — prod embedding backfill** | 🟡 grounding-quality (out-of-box vendor corpus only) | ready-for-human | Founder runs the off-CI backfill from a Tailnet node (CI can't reach the nomic-embed-text Ollama) → flips `apply-seeds.yml` embedding-coverage gate green, lifts grounding. Does **not** affect the stranger's-own-manual path (#2099 embeds on write). |
| **3** | **D2 — replay seam inert (7-cycle carry)** | 🟡 test-coverage | OPEN; runbook staged | Founder activates per `patches/2026-06-11-D4-replay-seam-activation.md` (live keys + PII eyeball) → activates `eval-replay-gate.yml`, gives `cp_citation_vendor_relevance` (#1858) its missing PR-time guard. |
| **4** | **E-2 / Gap-5 — staging has no human HTTPS front door** | 🟡 team-QA convenience (NOT stranger-facing) | OPEN; plan staged | Founder finishes `stg.factorylm.com` (`deploy-nginx-stg.yml` + Doppler `NEXTAUTH_URL`, plan 2026-06-15). Testers sign up on prod, which Smoke covers — so this is QA ergonomics, not a beta gate. |
| **5** | **Branch-protection: make `hub-e2e.yml` + signup-smoke required checks** | 🟡 enforcement-scope | unverifiable in-sandbox | Founder sets them as required status checks in GitHub repo settings (no `gh`/network in sandbox to confirm). Workflows already *run* on PR (#2082); the open question is whether they *block merge*. |
