## Lens E — Promotion pipeline (E10, prior run): GREEN → GREEN (held, verified on deploy truth)

Re-audited on deploy truth (`origin/main@944ef64d`; freshness-guard exit 3 STALE). E-scope
freshness: `.github/workflows` differs from the branch by exactly **one** file —
`apply-seeds.yml` (the D10 embedding-coverage gate, present on origin/main) — while
`docker-compose.staging.yml`, `docker-compose.staging-vps.yml` and `docs/migrations` match
origin/main. Baseline E9@2026-06-17. A real verification pass: E9 asserted "two-gate deploy
intact" and "staging usable"; E10 reads the workflow bodies and confirms both, with the exact
gating wiring.

### The two-gate deploy DAG (read from the workflow bodies — intact)

| Gate | Workflow | Wiring (verified on origin/main) |
|---|---|---|
| **Smoke** | `smoke-test.yml` | push:main + PR + dispatch. Playwright E2E against **both** `WEB_URL=factorylm.com` **and** `HUB_URL=app.factorylm.com`, **plus** the signup money-path (`playwright.signup.config.ts`: pricing → trial CTA → checkout → magic link). The stranger's front door, gated every push. |
| **Staging Gate** | `staging-gate.yml` | live E2E rubric vs the NeonDB **staging branch** on every PR to main (since 2026-05-18). |
| **Migration pre-gate** | `migration-verify.yml` | auto-applies `mira-hub/db/migrations/**` to the staging Neon branch on any migrations-PR, **landing first** so the Staging Gate sees the applied schema. Prod migs still go through `apply-migrations.yml`. |
| **Deploy** | `deploy-vps.yml` | `workflow_run:['Smoke Test']`; deploys **only if** `conclusion==success` **AND** the most-recent Staging Gate on the same commit passed. `environment: production`. Hotfix bypass needs `skip_staging_gate=true` + non-empty `skip_reason` → **auto-opens an audit issue**. |
| **Beta gate** | `beta-gate.yml` | dispatch + **weekly cron (Mon 07:00 UTC)** + PR. CI-enforces `tests/beta/beta_ready_upload_retrieval_citation.py` (xfail removed #2077). |
| **Hub e2e** | `hub-e2e.yml` | PR-to-main (paths-ignore) + dispatch (wired #2082). |

### Findings

| | Detail |
|---|---|
| **E-1 (staging Gap-1/Gap-3 CLOSED — E9 carry retired)** | Both staging compose files exist on origin/main: `docker-compose.staging.yml` (111 lines, local-dev CHARLIE bot-path) **and** `docker-compose.staging-vps.yml` (19 KB, the deployed always-on VPS stack — project `mira-staging`, offset ports `stg-mira-hub:4101`/pipeline:4099/web:4200, pointed at staging Neon `ep-polished-hall`, **not** prod). Staging bot is `@Mira_stagong_bot` (token `TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN_STG`), never `@FactoryLM_Diagnose`. `docs/environments.md` marks Gap-1 + Gap-3 closed. ⇒ root `CLAUDE.md` Environments table is **stale** (still tags both `*(TODO)*`) → staged `patches/2026-06-19-E10-claude-md-staging-todo-stale.patch` (apply-check CLEAN vs origin/main). |
| **E-2 (Gap-5 — the one open staging item, NOT a beta blocker)** | Staging has no human-usable HTTPS front door: the staging hub's `NEXTAUTH_URL` points at a Tailscale http IP, so browser/Google login fails — you can reach staging but can't sign in (`docs/environments.md` L48). Fix staged but not landed: `stg.factorylm.com` (`deployment/nginx-stg-factorylm.conf` + `deploy-nginx-stg.yml` + Doppler `NEXTAUTH_URL` + Google redirect URI; plan `docs/plans/2026-06-15-staging-usable-subdomain.md`). Impact = **team** manual staging QA, not the stranger flow (testers sign up on prod, which Smoke covers). Keeps E GREEN. |
