<details><summary>Prior D10 detail (retained)</summary>

## Lens D — Eval & test health (D10, prior run): YELLOW → YELLOW (held, strengthened)

Re-audited on deploy truth (`origin/main@944ef64d`; freshness-guard exit 3 STALE, but
`tests/eval` + `tests/beta` match origin/main **byte-for-byte**). Baseline D9@`14fe2732`;
**5 eval/test-relevant PRs landed this window** — D10 is a real change-audit, not a freeze.

### The window's headline: the embedding-coverage arc (root-cause fix + lock-in)

| PR | What | Effect on Lens D | Verdict |
|---|---|---|---|
| **#2085** (`1a47fe5a`) | backfill NULL embeddings so seeded chunks are retrievable | **Recovers D9's slip.** Q01 16→26 chunks; grounded 261→286. Reverses the 2026-06-17 Q01/Q10 dark-chunk miss that dropped the scorecard 50→49. | **Root-cause fix.** |
| **#2094/#2098** (`0f27e72b`) | seed-path guarantee — `apply-seeds.yml` embedding-coverage GATE + discipline | New **fail-loud CI gate**: corpus-wide NULL-count over curated retrieval types after seed applies. CI can't reach Tailnet Ollama → it VERIFIES (count only), backfill runs off-CI. By design stays RED-against-prod until #2093 runs (surfaces debt, never hides). | **New guard (honest RED).** |
| **#2099/#2100** (`a8fd43fa`) | embed-on-write for node-attachment chunks | The **stranger's-own-upload path now embeds on write** → retrievable → structurally protects the beta-gate retrieval/citation metric (#2077). | **Strengthens gate flow.** |
| **#2096/#2013** (`fc35c9f8`) | Hermes outside-in QA tooling + durable login helper on main | Widens the e2e proof surface (durable login). | Additive. |
| **#2108/#1993** (`cc4acfe0`) | onboarding-validate e2e walks the upload step | e2e now exercises the real upload door, not a stub. | Additive. |

### Two new guard tests — both sound (read-verified on origin/main)

1. **`tests/test_backfill_embeddings_guard.py`** (54 lines) — asserts `embed()` fails loud on a
   dimension mismatch vs `knowledge_entries.embedding` `vector(768)`, so a wrong model can't
   silently poison cosine similarity. Plain unit, always-on.
2. **`tests/test_embedding_coverage_canary.py`** (61 lines) — fails loud if curated retrieval
   types (`field-guide`/`integration_guide`/`component_template`) ever carry NULL embeddings
   again. Env-driven like the beta gate (SKIPS without `NEON_DATABASE_URL`, ASSERTS on
   dev/staging, **never prod**). The "build a canary, not a one-time fix" lock-in (cf. #1385).

### Findings

| | Detail |
|---|---|
| **D-1 (new, non-gate-breaking)** | `apply-seeds.yml` embedding-coverage gate is **RED-against-prod by design** until the founder runs the off-CI prod embedding backfill (**#2093, ready-for-human**) — ubuntu CI runners can't reach the nomic-embed-text Ollama on the Tailnet. This is honest surfaced debt, not a flaky gate. It degrades **out-of-box vendor** grounding quality, not the stranger's-own-manual flow. |
| **D-2 (standing, 7-cycle carry)** | Replay seam **still inert** — `.gitignore:241` ignores `tests/eval/fixtures/llm_replay/*.json`, no store committed on origin/main, `eval-replay-gate.yml` SKIPs with `::warning::`. So `cp_citation_vendor_relevance` (#1858 vendor-strip) remains the **one diagnostic invariant with no operable PR-time CI guard**. Runbook: `patches/2026-06-11-D4-replay-seam-activation.md`. Needs founder (live keys + PII eyeball). |
| **D-3 (scorecard freshness)** | Latest **committed** offline run is `2026-06-08T0229` = **50/57 (87%), 0 beta-critical fails** (No5xx/TurnBudget/CitGrond all green). The committed `runs/` dir stops at 06-08; the fresh number lives in the nightly job (D9 saw 49/57 on 06-17). #2085's backfill should recover that miss — trajectory is **improving**, not degrading. |

**KG insight (D10):** the nightly code graph indexes `_product_search()` — the literal
`embedding IS NOT NULL` clause that makes a NULL-embedding chunk **dark** (the failure
*mechanism*) — but indexes **none** of this window's guard surface
(`backfill_knowledge_embeddings.py`=0, coverage canary=0, `apply-seeds` gate=0; `"embedding
coverage"` / `"apply-seeds"` → []; a `"backfill"` search returns only the TS `uns`/`hierarchy`
backfills, not the new Python embedding backfill). The graph can show you *why* retrieval went
dark, never that it is now guarded — the precise reason Lens D must be read from workflows +
tests + `.gitignore`, not the code graph. Same **present-producer / missing-consumer** fingerprint
prior rounds named for the inert replay seam and the enforced beta-gate; this round it's the
dark-chunk **canary + gate** that are the measured drift. Sidecar: `kg/d10-findings.jsonl`
(+10 nodes / +5 edges).

